            </a>

        </div>

      <div class="signature-row">




              <h1 class="signature" translate="no">sendf(Connection, CmdFormat, Args, Opts)<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result">Result</span></h1>




          <span class="note">(since OTP 17.4)</span>


          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/common_test/src/ct_telnet.erl#L537" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">


        <div class="specs">
          <h4 class="specs-title">Types</h4>

            <pre translate="no">Connection = <a href="#t:connection/0">connection</a>()</pre>

            <pre translate="no">CmdFormat = <a href="../../../../lib/stdlib/doc/html/io.html#t:format/0">io:format</a>()</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Args = [<a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:term/0">term</a>()]</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Opts = [<a href="#t:newline_option/0">newline_option</a>()]</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Result = ok | {error, Reason}</pre>

            <pre translate="no">Reason = <a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:term/0">term</a>()</pre>

        </div>


<p>Sends a Telnet command and returns immediately (uses a format string and a list
of arguments to build the command).</p><p>For details, see <a href="#send/3"><code class="inline">ct_telnet:send/3</code></a>.</p>
  </section>
</section>

